1
00:00:12,250 --> 00:00:13,749
[Team Leader Baek Su Jeong]

2
00:00:13,750 --> 00:00:16,510
[Moon Ga Young]

3
00:00:17,720 --> 00:00:19,099
[Director Ban Ju Yeon]

4
00:00:19,100 --> 00:00:21,849
[Choi Hyeon Wook]

5
00:00:21,850 --> 00:00:23,840
[Yongsung's successor. [The new chaebol director?]

6
00:00:25,780 --> 00:00:28,000
[Im Se Mi]

7
00:00:28,850 --> 00:00:30,970
[Kwak Shi Yang]

8
00:00:41,350 --> 00:00:44,969
[My Dearest Enemy]

9
00:00:44,970 --> 00:00:47,539
[This series is fictional.]

10
00:00:47,540 --> 00:00:50,449
[Characters and settings are fictional.]

11
00:00:50,450 --> 00:00:52,340
[Chapter 8]

12
00:01:02,120 --> 00:01:04,319
In that case...

13
00:01:04,320 --> 00:01:06,209
thing...

14
00:01:06,210 --> 00:01:07,990
Let me let you go.

15
00:01:08,880 --> 00:01:11,169
Okay. I'll go.

16
00:01:11,170 --> 00:01:12,550
Okay.

17
00:01:40,290 --> 00:01:42,779
- Why...? - I think...

18
00:01:42,780 --> 00:01:45,289
I want to ask you something.

19
00:01:45,290 --> 00:01:47,999
Really? What is it?

20
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:51,749
It's a bit strange to talk here.

21
00:01:51,750 --> 00:01:52,959
Shall we go for a walk?

22
00:01:52,960 --> 00:01:54,659
I would be very happy.

23
00:01:54,660 --> 00:01:55,789
You can ask me anything.

24
00:01:55,790 --> 00:01:58,050
I will answer every question.

25
00:02:08,660 --> 00:02:11,180
What did you want to ask me...?

26
00:02:16,820 --> 00:02:19,769
What should I do with your belongings?

27
00:02:19,770 --> 00:02:22,139
I've put it in my attic for now.

28
00:02:22,140 --> 00:02:25,349
Don't you need to find a place to stay somewhere?

29
00:02:25,350 --> 00:02:26,829
I am not sure.

30
00:02:26,830 --> 00:02:31,140
If I were to take a position in my own name, the president might find out.

31
00:02:32,050 --> 00:02:34,550
Ah, I understand.

32
00:02:37,420 --> 00:02:40,459
If that's alright, can I leave them there?

33
00:02:40,460 --> 00:02:43,360
I'll feel comfortable if I'm at your house.

34
00:02:44,140 --> 00:02:46,050
That would also be a good excuse to see you.

35
00:03:02,860 --> 00:03:05,950
You say such things without any shame.

36
00:03:23,990 --> 00:03:27,500
I'll go inside then.

37
00:03:30,240 --> 00:03:31,740
Ben...

38
00:03:32,830 --> 00:03:35,379
I have something to ask you.

39
00:03:35,380 --> 00:03:37,309
Really?

40
00:03:37,310 --> 00:03:38,650
Yes.

41
00:03:46,620 --> 00:03:49,460
What did you want to ask me?

42
00:03:52,430 --> 00:03:55,799
I think you're very close to that woman.

43
00:03:55,800 --> 00:03:56,959
Jin, do you love me?

44
00:03:56,960 --> 00:03:58,569
We've been close since we were kids.

45
00:03:58,570 --> 00:04:00,720
We met while playing a video game.

46
00:04:02,360 --> 00:04:05,040
Was this the game where you met your first love?

47
00:04:06,170 --> 00:04:07,580
Yes.

48
00:04:11,080 --> 00:04:12,970
What is the name of that game?

49
00:04:41,750 --> 00:04:45,309
I think you're close to Chef Kim.

50
00:04:45,310 --> 00:04:47,960
Yes, he's my mother's friend-

51
00:04:51,870 --> 00:04:54,569
Oh dear, are you alright?

52
00:04:54,570 --> 00:04:55,899
It was a motorcycle.

53
00:04:55,900 --> 00:04:57,390
Yes.

54
00:05:03,720 --> 00:05:07,819
Anyway, we were childhood friends.

55
00:05:07,820 --> 00:05:11,049
Ah, I understand.

56
00:05:11,050 --> 00:05:12,949
Wait a minute.

57
00:05:12,950 --> 00:05:17,420
So you asked him to ask questions about me?

58
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:20,739
I had no other option then.

59
00:05:20,740 --> 00:05:23,700
You knew a lot about my secret.

60
00:05:30,700 --> 00:05:32,300
Did they leave?

61
00:05:34,270 --> 00:05:37,320
Yes, the cat is gone.

62
00:05:39,580 --> 00:05:41,580
Was it a cat?

63
00:05:50,540 --> 00:05:52,589
Maybe I overreacted.

64
00:05:52,590 --> 00:05:54,399
A little?

65
00:05:54,400 --> 00:05:57,629
Should we do this when there aren't many people around?

66
00:05:57,630 --> 00:05:59,429
We might run into my father.

67
00:05:59,430 --> 00:06:01,709
Being careful won't hurt.

68
00:06:01,710 --> 00:06:04,449
Getting caught by someone at work would be worse.

69
00:06:04,450 --> 00:06:06,549
There are a lot of people here, you know.

70
00:06:06,550 --> 00:06:09,819
The headquarters employs 8,000 people, and including subsidiaries, the total number of employees is 100,000.

71
00:06:09,820 --> 00:06:13,019
You never know when or where you're going to run into someone. Don't you agree?

72
00:06:13,020 --> 00:06:14,469
You convinced me.

73
00:06:14,470 --> 00:06:16,100
Wait.

74
00:06:21,620 --> 00:06:23,319
- Let's go. - Is there no one around?

75
00:06:23,320 --> 00:06:24,740
Yes.

76
00:06:47,790 --> 00:06:50,479
I really need to leave now.

77
00:06:50,480 --> 00:06:53,089
Drive home safely. Call me when you get there.

78
00:06:53,090 --> 00:06:56,120
Okay. Good night.

79
00:07:26,630 --> 00:07:28,170
Yes!

80
00:07:38,210 --> 00:07:39,910
Peace?

81
00:07:40,930 --> 00:07:43,930
Does that mean something like rock 'n' roll?

82
00:07:49,860 --> 00:07:51,839
I love you.

83
00:07:51,840 --> 00:07:53,769
This guy is crazy.

84
00:07:53,770 --> 00:07:55,930
That's what it means in sign language.

85
00:07:58,180 --> 00:08:01,860
Really. She knows how to make me laugh.

86
00:08:37,670 --> 00:08:39,839
She knows how to drive me crazy.

87
00:08:39,840 --> 00:08:41,940
[Grace]

88
00:08:43,900 --> 00:08:45,039
Excuse me.

89
00:08:45,040 --> 00:08:47,619
Yes sir. Do you need anything?

90
00:08:47,620 --> 00:08:49,990
Alcohol? Water? Snacks?

91
00:08:51,730 --> 00:08:56,279
Instead, could I have your number?

92
00:08:56,280 --> 00:08:57,640
Sir?

93
00:08:58,740 --> 00:09:01,530
I'd like to see you somewhere else sometimes.

94
00:09:03,350 --> 00:09:05,390
[Lee Hyeong Geun, CEO of AZ Investment Securities]

95
00:09:09,980 --> 00:09:13,189
I'm afraid that won't be possible.

96
00:09:13,190 --> 00:09:14,579
Why not?

97
00:09:14,580 --> 00:09:15,879
Because I'm a customer?

98
00:09:15,880 --> 00:09:19,039
No. I don't care if you're a customer.

99
00:09:19,040 --> 00:09:22,589
I'm simply not interested in you.

100
00:09:22,590 --> 00:09:24,546
- D-You're not interested in me? - No.

101
00:09:24,547 --> 00:09:28,510
Let me know if you need anything other than my number.

102
00:09:37,750 --> 00:09:39,650
[Kim Shin Won]

103
00:09:52,550 --> 00:09:54,320
[Grace]

104
00:09:55,410 --> 00:09:56,899
[Unfollow]

105
00:09:56,900 --> 00:09:58,970
[Unfollow Confirm]

106
00:10:00,850 --> 00:10:03,520
I probably won't see him again.

107
00:10:09,020 --> 00:10:10,640
Kim Shin Won.

108
00:10:11,320 --> 00:10:13,009
- It's been a long time. - Yes.

109
00:10:13,010 --> 00:10:16,149
Did we last meet at our last gathering?

110
00:10:16,150 --> 00:10:18,099
Are you alone? Where's your girlfriend?

111
00:10:18,100 --> 00:10:20,259
My girlfriend?

112
00:10:20,260 --> 00:10:21,709
We broke up a while ago.

113
00:10:21,710 --> 00:10:23,179
How many hours has it been?

114
00:10:23,180 --> 00:10:24,819
Has it been at least 24 hours?

115
00:10:24,820 --> 00:10:26,339
Joking.

116
00:10:26,340 --> 00:10:28,220
I'm going to give this up.

117
00:10:32,780 --> 00:10:34,979
Have you heard of Ha Jin?

118
00:10:34,980 --> 00:10:37,219
Her husband cheated on her and they got divorced.

119
00:10:37,220 --> 00:10:38,899
Crazy! Are you serious?

120
00:10:38,900 --> 00:10:41,339
I never thought he would do that.

121
00:10:41,340 --> 00:10:43,289
They had been campus couples since first grade.

122
00:10:43,290 --> 00:10:45,579
I know. You can never truly know people.

123
00:10:45,580 --> 00:10:47,549
I feel so sorry for him.

124
00:10:47,550 --> 00:10:48,769
I am good.

125
00:10:48,770 --> 00:10:50,419
- Ha Jin. - You came early.

126
00:10:50,420 --> 00:10:54,079
Hey, I heard about your husband.

127
00:10:54,080 --> 00:10:55,799
Are you really okay?

128
00:10:55,800 --> 00:10:57,529
Yes, I'm fine.

129
00:10:57,530 --> 00:11:01,619
At first I was angry, but I haven't felt any emotions since we divorced.

130
00:11:01,620 --> 00:11:04,399
- Ha Jin. - What do you mean you're fine?

131
00:11:04,400 --> 00:11:06,319
You don't have to put on an act in front of us.

132
00:11:06,320 --> 00:11:07,649
Right.

133
00:11:07,650 --> 00:11:09,159
No, I'm serious.

134
00:11:09,160 --> 00:11:10,839
Divorce is not a trivial matter.

135
00:11:10,840 --> 00:11:14,349
Those who cheat should be completely eradicated.

136
00:11:14,350 --> 00:11:15,969
Hey, calm him down.

137
00:11:15,970 --> 00:11:17,879
Hey...

138
00:11:17,880 --> 00:11:19,480
Let's go. Let's go.

139
00:11:31,410 --> 00:11:35,080
Huh? So we're meeting here now?

140
00:11:42,760 --> 00:11:44,970
Would you like some sweets with me?

141
00:11:58,300 --> 00:12:00,819
Meeting you here is a bit...

142
00:12:00,820 --> 00:12:02,730
Does it feel like fate?

143
00:12:05,820 --> 00:12:07,340
Yes.

144
00:12:08,460 --> 00:12:13,319
I was angry because my friends were telling me to get married.

145
00:12:13,320 --> 00:12:17,419
That's why I came up here. But you were here.

146
00:12:17,420 --> 00:12:19,409
So, I guess...

147
00:12:19,410 --> 00:12:21,459
I came here angry, too.

148
00:12:21,460 --> 00:12:25,820
Why? Did your friends tell you to get married too?

149
00:12:26,680 --> 00:12:29,149
Who would say that to someone who's recently divorced?

150
00:12:29,150 --> 00:12:32,230
Ah, yes. That's right.

151
00:12:37,190 --> 00:12:39,819
With my ex-wife...

152
00:12:39,820 --> 00:12:44,569
I dated him for over 10 years, since first grade, and we got married.

153
00:12:44,570 --> 00:12:46,380
You had been together for a long time.

154
00:12:47,380 --> 00:12:51,049
Because we had known each other for a long time, I thought I knew him well.

155
00:12:51,050 --> 00:12:53,709
But I guess marriage was another story.

156
00:12:53,710 --> 00:12:56,369
He cheated on me in less than six months.

157
00:12:56,370 --> 00:12:58,099
After he moved to another city.

158
00:12:58,100 --> 00:12:59,439
What a stick figure.

159
00:12:59,440 --> 00:13:01,340
I know.

160
00:13:02,360 --> 00:13:04,319
He's a stick figure.

161
00:13:04,320 --> 00:13:07,799
I was really fine after getting rid of him.

162
00:13:07,800 --> 00:13:10,619
But everyone says I won't be okay.

163
00:13:10,620 --> 00:13:13,250
Should I pretend I'm not okay?

164
00:13:13,900 --> 00:13:17,169
If you're really fine, don't bother.

165
00:13:17,170 --> 00:13:18,899
I know.

166
00:13:18,900 --> 00:13:21,670
I wish they believed me like you believed them.

167
00:13:23,060 --> 00:13:25,909
I was angry about things like that too.

168
00:13:25,910 --> 00:13:31,070
I've been sincere in everything, but they all say I wasn't sincere.

169
00:13:32,100 --> 00:13:35,579
You know how you feel better than anyone.

170
00:13:35,580 --> 00:13:37,569
I know.

171
00:13:37,570 --> 00:13:42,290
I know how I feel better than anyone.

172
00:13:46,530 --> 00:13:48,500
Really...

173
00:13:51,040 --> 00:13:53,550
I have always been sincere.

174
00:14:29,540 --> 00:14:31,600
Do you want to sleep with me?

175
00:14:36,390 --> 00:14:41,043
That you could sleep with me again, just like last time...

176
00:14:41,055 --> 00:14:45,039
...but you said you didn't want to go out with me.

177
00:14:45,040 --> 00:14:46,159
Do you still feel the same way?

178
00:14:46,160 --> 00:14:47,959
If I said yes, would you reject me?

179
00:14:47,960 --> 00:14:50,600
Yes, I refuse.

180
00:15:00,090 --> 00:15:02,729
You rejected me, but you returned my kiss.

181
00:15:02,730 --> 00:15:04,799
You should have pushed me.

182
00:15:04,800 --> 00:15:07,450
There's no way I can push you away.

183
00:15:08,710 --> 00:15:11,000
Do you like me that much?

184
00:15:12,400 --> 00:15:14,450
This is not good.

185
00:15:15,050 --> 00:15:18,520
You'll have to go out with me seriously.

186
00:15:21,310 --> 00:15:23,550
Follow me too.

187
00:15:25,070 --> 00:15:26,760
Don't you want?

188
00:15:30,140 --> 00:15:34,300
I want to. Because I like you.

189
00:15:58,900 --> 00:16:01,659
You said you had a meeting. What are you doing here?

190
00:16:01,660 --> 00:16:04,259
I have a brief moment to see you.

191
00:16:04,260 --> 00:16:07,770
- Was there no traffic? - No. I arrived safely.

192
00:16:09,920 --> 00:16:11,659
Su Jeong.

193
00:16:11,660 --> 00:16:13,939
When did you leave the house...?

194
00:16:13,940 --> 00:16:15,590
Director?

195
00:16:19,010 --> 00:16:20,460
Baba.

196
00:16:22,630 --> 00:16:26,779
What brought you here today, Director?

197
00:16:26,780 --> 00:16:28,860
Well, actually...

198
00:16:30,310 --> 00:16:31,549
How are you, Dad?

199
00:16:31,550 --> 00:16:32,979
I am good.

200
00:16:32,980 --> 00:16:35,489
You saw me yesterday, you know.

201
00:16:35,490 --> 00:16:36,899
Packages...

202
00:16:36,900 --> 00:16:39,919
The packages in my room belong to him.

203
00:16:39,920 --> 00:16:41,939
The company's confidential documents.

204
00:16:41,940 --> 00:16:43,329
I understand.

205
00:16:43,330 --> 00:16:47,189
Because Ms. Baek is the employee I trust the most.

206
00:16:47,190 --> 00:16:49,189
That's why I keep them at your house.

207
00:16:49,190 --> 00:16:51,709
Thank you for your permission.

208
00:16:51,710 --> 00:16:54,129
We're just keeping it secret.

209
00:16:54,130 --> 00:16:55,910
Meanwhile, why...

210
00:16:57,070 --> 00:17:02,010
The document I need to check today happened to be here. That's why I'm here.

211
00:17:06,160 --> 00:17:08,520
But on the weekend.

212
00:17:12,300 --> 00:17:14,330
I understand.

213
00:17:16,950 --> 00:17:19,769
You're a workaholic too.

214
00:17:19,770 --> 00:17:22,769
You're definitely Yongsung's leader.

215
00:17:22,770 --> 00:17:26,099
Actually, Su Jeong is a serious workaholic too.

216
00:17:26,100 --> 00:17:27,719
He works until late hours and on weekends as well.

217
00:17:27,720 --> 00:17:29,249
Unbelievable.

218
00:17:29,250 --> 00:17:33,819
But you must like him because he works so hard.

219
00:17:33,820 --> 00:17:35,610
Yes, me...

220
00:17:36,550 --> 00:17:38,809
I love him.

221
00:17:38,810 --> 00:17:42,009
Instead of standing here, why don't you come inside?

222
00:17:42,010 --> 00:17:44,199
- What are you doing, Su Jeong? - Huh?

223
00:17:44,200 --> 00:17:46,029
- W-Why...? - Help him get inside.

224
00:17:46,030 --> 00:17:48,180
I'll take this out first.

225
00:17:51,720 --> 00:17:53,720
It won't be a problem, right?

226
00:17:58,610 --> 00:18:00,580
Come in.

227
00:18:12,900 --> 00:18:15,389
Is this your room?

228
00:18:15,390 --> 00:18:16,760
Yes.

229
00:18:28,490 --> 00:18:30,419
Toggaengyi.

230
00:18:30,420 --> 00:18:33,119
You kept him safe.

231
00:18:33,120 --> 00:18:34,800
Certainly.

232
00:18:38,630 --> 00:18:40,259
Don't you want the document?

233
00:18:40,260 --> 00:18:42,029
You said you were looking for an important document.

234
00:18:42,030 --> 00:18:43,999
Ah, Belgian.

235
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:46,679
I forgot. I need to find it now.

236
00:18:46,680 --> 00:18:49,469
Key... Key...

237
00:18:49,470 --> 00:18:51,100
He was around here.

238
00:18:52,390 --> 00:18:53,959
It was somewhere around here.

239
00:18:53,960 --> 00:18:55,740
Where...

240
00:18:56,900 --> 00:18:59,200
I found it! The key.

241
00:19:01,090 --> 00:19:02,880
The key point.

242
00:19:04,100 --> 00:19:06,539
Come when you're finished. I'll cut some fruit.

243
00:19:06,540 --> 00:19:08,180
Okay.

244
00:19:28,110 --> 00:19:30,469
Did you find the document?

245
00:19:30,470 --> 00:19:32,880
Yes, I'm looking.

246
00:19:48,080 --> 00:19:50,419
You're trapped here.

247
00:19:50,420 --> 00:19:52,289
Keep this place safe for me.

248
00:19:52,290 --> 00:19:55,260
You're the smartest of them all.

249
00:20:08,620 --> 00:20:11,310
Everything is well hidden.

250
00:20:16,190 --> 00:20:19,240
I'm curious about something.

251
00:20:21,170 --> 00:20:23,150
What's this?

252
00:20:26,240 --> 00:20:29,649
I-I don't know. What could it be...?

253
00:20:29,650 --> 00:20:32,840
Dad must be waiting. Go out and eat some fruit.

254
00:20:39,720 --> 00:20:41,400
I am at home.

255
00:20:43,240 --> 00:20:45,330
- Hey. - Hey, hey!

256
00:20:49,800 --> 00:20:51,979
G-Get out of here.

257
00:20:51,980 --> 00:20:54,360
Please go.

258
00:21:03,760 --> 00:21:06,169
The bathroom door handle is loose.

259
00:21:06,170 --> 00:21:08,059
Sometimes it opens even when it's locked.

260
00:21:08,060 --> 00:21:10,589
It should have happened while you were inside.

261
00:21:10,590 --> 00:21:12,169
I need to fix it immediately.

262
00:21:12,170 --> 00:21:14,019
I'll fix it later.

263
00:21:14,020 --> 00:21:15,549
You must have been scared.

264
00:21:15,550 --> 00:21:17,639
I was scared, but...

265
00:21:17,640 --> 00:21:18,809
No problem.

266
00:21:18,810 --> 00:21:21,779
I haven't lost my dignity as a human being.

267
00:21:21,780 --> 00:21:23,100
Okay.

268
00:21:24,500 --> 00:21:26,400
Take some.

269
00:21:31,400 --> 00:21:33,429
Why did you come to our house?

270
00:21:33,430 --> 00:21:35,269
Here is an important document.

271
00:21:35,270 --> 00:21:36,469
He came to pick it up.

272
00:21:36,470 --> 00:21:38,109
Is it an important document?

273
00:21:38,110 --> 00:21:39,529
Why didn't you just take it and leave?

274
00:21:39,530 --> 00:21:42,529
Why did you mark your area?

275
00:21:42,530 --> 00:21:45,260
- Marking my territory? - You little-

276
00:21:51,790 --> 00:21:55,889
Baek Su Bin, why are you being so rude to the guest?

277
00:21:55,890 --> 00:22:01,049
Why didn't you just wander around your apartment? Why are you here?

278
00:22:01,050 --> 00:22:03,149
I am visiting my home.

279
00:22:03,150 --> 00:22:05,589
Don't touch me. My hair is falling out.

280
00:22:05,590 --> 00:22:09,659
Director, eat something. Here you go.

281
00:22:09,660 --> 00:22:11,669
It's getting colder.

282
00:22:11,670 --> 00:22:14,279
I'm sorry, but I have a meeting.

283
00:22:14,280 --> 00:22:15,699
I'm leaving now.

284
00:22:15,700 --> 00:22:17,690
Eat one anyway.

285
00:22:19,790 --> 00:22:21,280
Okay.

286
00:22:31,660 --> 00:22:33,459
I'm leaving now.

287
00:22:33,460 --> 00:22:35,690
Thank you for inviting me.

288
00:22:36,730 --> 00:22:38,410
Oh, okay.

289
00:22:51,820 --> 00:22:54,970
What are you doing? Stop.

290
00:22:56,830 --> 00:22:59,359
Are you two already dating?

291
00:22:59,360 --> 00:23:01,069
Why did you invite him here so early?

292
00:23:01,070 --> 00:23:02,239
This is inappropriate.

293
00:23:02,240 --> 00:23:05,861
What are you saying? Didn't you hear my father? He was here for a document...

294
00:23:05,873 --> 00:23:10,059
...I know. The fact that he's here means you're serious.

295
00:23:10,060 --> 00:23:11,369
You fooled your father too.

296
00:23:11,370 --> 00:23:13,739
Did you agree to sneak out or something?

297
00:23:13,740 --> 00:23:17,809
Hey, you—big sister, what happens if you get caught doing this?

298
00:23:17,810 --> 00:23:21,609
My dad and I are fine, but what if your coworkers find out?

299
00:23:21,610 --> 00:23:24,629
The director's family will find out sooner or later.

300
00:23:24,630 --> 00:23:29,519
Maybe he's sincere, but his family won't like you.

301
00:23:29,520 --> 00:23:33,429
What if they splashed water on you and then dropped you an envelope?

302
00:23:33,430 --> 00:23:38,429
Would you cry and say, "Just let us fall in love"? Is that it?

303
00:23:38,430 --> 00:23:41,449
Are you watching TV series instead of studying?

304
00:23:41,450 --> 00:23:42,929
We're not going out, I told you.

305
00:23:42,930 --> 00:23:45,099
This won't happen.

306
00:23:45,100 --> 00:23:49,319
And even if it did, it wouldn't matter.

307
00:23:49,320 --> 00:23:52,859
- You're crazy. - Stop talking nonsense and get out.

308
00:23:52,860 --> 00:23:54,349
Okay.

309
00:23:54,350 --> 00:23:56,489
I'm sure you can figure it out.

310
00:23:56,490 --> 00:23:58,880
But, Sister,

311
00:23:59,530 --> 00:24:01,829
Really...

312
00:24:01,830 --> 00:24:05,749
I don't want you to get hurt.

313
00:24:05,750 --> 00:24:09,420
I'm worried about you right now.

314
00:24:20,600 --> 00:24:24,150
I have a wonderful little brother.

315
00:24:27,080 --> 00:24:30,270
Oh dear, who would marry her?

316
00:24:35,060 --> 00:24:38,449
Isn't he the heir to your company or something?

317
00:24:38,450 --> 00:24:40,429
You showed me your picture last time.

318
00:24:40,430 --> 00:24:42,879
Great. What is he doing here?

319
00:24:42,880 --> 00:24:44,989
He must have come to buy dessert.

320
00:24:44,990 --> 00:24:47,790
Are the Chaeboller eating this dessert?

321
00:24:51,390 --> 00:24:55,320
There are too many employees.

322
00:24:57,040 --> 00:24:58,599
You said it would be difficult to get.

323
00:24:58,600 --> 00:25:01,449
There are too many people inside.

324
00:25:01,450 --> 00:25:03,809
I'm glad I ordered in advance.

325
00:25:03,810 --> 00:25:05,650
Let's go.

326
00:25:08,690 --> 00:25:11,099
It will be here in about five minutes.

327
00:25:11,100 --> 00:25:12,670
Okay.

328
00:25:16,130 --> 00:25:17,910
Chief Kwon,

329
00:25:19,200 --> 00:25:23,900
You started in Yongsung 20 years and three months ago.

330
00:25:24,670 --> 00:25:26,059
As expected.

331
00:25:26,060 --> 00:25:28,400
That's absolutely true.

332
00:25:30,300 --> 00:25:34,699
Meanwhile, my daughter is already in middle school.

333
00:25:34,700 --> 00:25:37,300
Time really flies.

334
00:25:38,240 --> 00:25:44,149
You remained loyal to the president throughout this long period.

335
00:25:44,150 --> 00:25:47,339
It must have been possible because you genuinely respected her.

336
00:25:47,340 --> 00:25:49,820
I'm glad you accepted this.

337
00:25:51,220 --> 00:25:58,199
But why did you say that the president would visit me that day?

338
00:25:58,200 --> 00:26:02,400
You went against his word and helped me. Why?

339
00:26:03,990 --> 00:26:05,839
I didn't know...

340
00:26:05,840 --> 00:26:09,399
I helped you, Director.

341
00:26:09,400 --> 00:26:14,409
Just in case, I didn't want to delay her next appointment.

342
00:26:14,410 --> 00:26:16,560
That's why I called you.

343
00:26:17,610 --> 00:26:22,440
But in the end, something happened and it was delayed.

344
00:26:23,870 --> 00:26:25,550
Director.

345
00:26:26,350 --> 00:26:27,619
Yes.

346
00:26:27,620 --> 00:26:33,929
I want someone to be Yongsung's successor, someone who will carry on his vision.

347
00:26:33,930 --> 00:26:38,719
And I've never met anyone else who resembles him as much as you do.

348
00:26:38,720 --> 00:26:40,950
At least not yet.

349
00:26:41,650 --> 00:26:43,699
Well...

350
00:26:43,700 --> 00:26:49,440
I hope you won't disappoint the president any further.

351
00:26:52,180 --> 00:26:53,569
Don't worry.

352
00:26:53,570 --> 00:26:56,640
This won't happen.

353
00:27:05,540 --> 00:27:08,039
He is the CEO of Arteta Asia.

354
00:27:08,040 --> 00:27:09,299
Ben Ban Ju Yeon.

355
00:27:09,300 --> 00:27:12,159
I wanted to meet you earlier, but here we are.

356
00:27:12,160 --> 00:27:13,670
This...

357
00:27:14,360 --> 00:27:16,679
for your daughter.

358
00:27:16,680 --> 00:27:19,169
I can't say no to that.

359
00:27:19,170 --> 00:27:22,870
My daughter wanted to try this while she was in Korea.

360
00:27:36,040 --> 00:27:37,949
Here you go.

361
00:27:37,950 --> 00:27:39,119
Thank you.

362
00:27:39,120 --> 00:27:40,999
I'm a bit forgetful.

363
00:27:41,000 --> 00:27:43,869
I can help you from now on, right?

364
00:27:43,870 --> 00:27:45,550
Sounds good.

365
00:27:47,050 --> 00:27:49,809
I didn't ask you yesterday.

366
00:27:49,810 --> 00:27:51,929
You said you didn't want a serious relationship.

367
00:27:51,930 --> 00:27:54,410
Why did you change your mind?

368
00:27:55,650 --> 00:27:57,260
At random.

369
00:27:58,100 --> 00:28:01,379
I realized there was no reason for me not to see you.

370
00:28:01,380 --> 00:28:05,050
You like me and I like you.

371
00:28:08,000 --> 00:28:10,029
I just don't want anything complicated.

372
00:28:10,030 --> 00:28:12,088
Depending on the relationship, you hope, you dream...

373
00:28:12,100 --> 00:28:14,169
...you'll be disappointed, you'll deceive, and you'll be hurt.

374
00:28:14,170 --> 00:28:15,609
Isn't this terrible?

375
00:28:15,610 --> 00:28:17,489
If you're happy, that's good.

376
00:28:17,490 --> 00:28:20,710
If not, forget it. That's all I want.

377
00:28:21,380 --> 00:28:24,590
I thought it would be possible with you.

378
00:28:25,590 --> 00:28:26,839
You are right.

379
00:28:26,840 --> 00:28:30,470
You date someone to be happy.

380
00:28:33,690 --> 00:28:35,459
He arrived.

381
00:28:35,460 --> 00:28:38,149
Yes, I'm about to leave.

382
00:28:38,150 --> 00:28:39,569
What about you, Baek Soo Jeong?

383
00:28:39,570 --> 00:28:42,279
I'm going to work too.

384
00:28:42,280 --> 00:28:45,769
I'll see you at work soon.

385
00:28:45,770 --> 00:28:48,799
So you know we need to be more careful, right?

386
00:28:48,800 --> 00:28:50,389
Did you forget?

387
00:28:50,390 --> 00:28:53,599
I have kept my private life secret my entire life.

388
00:28:53,600 --> 00:28:55,599
I'll leave them to guess.

389
00:28:55,600 --> 00:28:58,789
We won't get caught. Don't worry.

390
00:28:58,790 --> 00:29:00,329
But I caught you.

391
00:29:00,330 --> 00:29:04,229
This means we are destined to be together.

392
00:29:04,230 --> 00:29:06,029
You said we were unlucky.

393
00:29:06,030 --> 00:29:08,089
Anyway, you shouldn't let on.

394
00:29:08,090 --> 00:29:10,179
I won't let on.

395
00:29:10,180 --> 00:29:11,379
Never.

396
00:29:11,380 --> 00:29:13,429
I won't either.

397
00:29:13,430 --> 00:29:15,260
Never.

398
00:29:25,190 --> 00:29:26,749
Hello, Team Leader.

399
00:29:26,750 --> 00:29:27,869
Hello.

400
00:29:27,870 --> 00:29:29,980
Hello.

401
00:30:01,760 --> 00:30:03,400
Team Leader.

402
00:30:05,310 --> 00:30:07,409
How did your blind date go?

403
00:30:07,410 --> 00:30:09,449
Did you have a date?

404
00:30:09,450 --> 00:30:11,539
- Excuse me? - You seemed to like him.

405
00:30:11,540 --> 00:30:13,300
Really?

406
00:30:16,100 --> 00:30:20,099
Assistant Manager Yang, you must be wrong.

407
00:30:20,100 --> 00:30:21,799
I rejected him. Completely.

408
00:30:21,800 --> 00:30:24,330
I cut it off completely.

409
00:30:41,230 --> 00:30:42,810
I think.

410
00:30:50,300 --> 00:30:54,939
I guess you can't impress every man.

411
00:30:54,940 --> 00:30:57,469
I think an older man would suit you better.

412
00:30:57,470 --> 00:30:59,750
W-Why...?

413
00:31:00,680 --> 00:31:04,110
Because you're so confident in yourself, it makes you...

414
00:31:04,122 --> 00:31:07,899
...an older person who is generous and kind would be more suitable.

415
00:31:07,900 --> 00:31:09,379
Yes, yes.

416
00:31:09,380 --> 00:31:12,929
And it shouldn't be too high-quality either.

417
00:31:12,930 --> 00:31:14,179
Why is this?

418
00:31:14,180 --> 00:31:15,529
Think.

419
00:31:15,530 --> 00:31:18,649
He needs to support his career.

420
00:31:18,650 --> 00:31:20,990
If he's obsessed with his reputation and success...

421
00:31:21,002 --> 00:31:23,039
...if that happens, it will be very tiring for both of you.

422
00:31:23,040 --> 00:31:26,079
Wouldn't it be great if we were both good at our jobs?

423
00:31:26,080 --> 00:31:28,949
I didn't want to say it because it's so obvious.

424
00:31:28,950 --> 00:31:31,439
You know the guy from the comic book you're talking about?

425
00:31:31,440 --> 00:31:35,129
Is he the kind of guy who kisses you and then says he's forgotten you?

426
00:31:35,130 --> 00:31:36,349
You can't date someone like him.

427
00:31:36,350 --> 00:31:38,159
That kind of man is the worst.

428
00:31:38,160 --> 00:31:39,439
Absolutely the worst.

429
00:31:39,440 --> 00:31:41,229
What kind of main character is this?

430
00:31:41,230 --> 00:31:44,299
Don't read comic books like that. They're bad for you.

431
00:31:44,300 --> 00:31:46,169
I know. I know.

432
00:31:46,170 --> 00:31:51,289
To be honest, I don't just want you dating someone at work.

433
00:31:51,290 --> 00:31:54,879
That's why I don't want you to resign.

434
00:31:54,880 --> 00:31:59,239
How could the assistant principal possibly be dating someone at work?

435
00:31:59,240 --> 00:32:03,369
She said office romance is hell.

436
00:32:03,370 --> 00:32:06,359
This is hell. Isn't it, Team Leader?

437
00:32:06,360 --> 00:32:09,169
- Did I say that? - Yes, this is hell.

438
00:32:09,170 --> 00:32:11,059
That's good to hear then.

439
00:32:11,060 --> 00:32:13,349
It's impossible for him to do something like that.

440
00:32:13,350 --> 00:32:14,919
Hell?

441
00:32:14,920 --> 00:32:17,180
Why did I say that?

442
00:32:31,870 --> 00:32:34,289
Na Na, where is Assistant Manager Yang?

443
00:32:34,290 --> 00:32:35,429
He hasn't been here for a while.

444
00:32:35,430 --> 00:32:38,110
Ah, in the director's office.

445
00:33:04,760 --> 00:33:07,890
So, Director?

446
00:33:09,500 --> 00:33:12,530
Direct-Director!

447
00:33:43,120 --> 00:33:50,329
Team Leader Baek, who prints and copies like this these days?

448
00:33:50,330 --> 00:33:52,319
It must be tiring.

449
00:33:52,320 --> 00:33:53,909
For me.

450
00:33:53,910 --> 00:33:56,220
For you too.

451
00:33:57,110 --> 00:33:59,839
I'll pick it up when you're finished.

452
00:33:59,840 --> 00:34:01,340
Okay.

453
00:34:12,940 --> 00:34:16,419
Team Leader - this... - Director!

454
00:34:16,420 --> 00:34:19,079
How can you have no practical skills at all?

455
00:34:19,080 --> 00:34:21,660
How can you not know how to make a copy?

456
00:34:23,360 --> 00:34:30,670
Look. Feed the paper like this, press the button, and the paper will come out.

457
00:34:32,560 --> 00:34:34,309
The letters are black and the paper is white.

458
00:34:34,310 --> 00:34:36,080
Go ahead and approve it.

459
00:34:36,910 --> 00:34:38,410
Git.

460
00:34:39,050 --> 00:34:40,680
Okay.

461
00:34:43,700 --> 00:34:46,420
How will he survive in this world?

462
00:34:53,420 --> 00:34:56,329
Team Leader, are you going to be a Director Killer again?

463
00:34:56,330 --> 00:34:58,870
Hala varis o.

464
00:34:59,740 --> 00:35:02,759
However, he/she needs to know how to make copies.

465
00:35:02,760 --> 00:35:04,389
Doesn't he know how to do it?

466
00:35:04,390 --> 00:35:07,269
I wasn't surprised. He didn't know how to grind either.

467
00:35:07,270 --> 00:35:10,039
I had a hard time because he was clinging to me all morning.

468
00:35:10,040 --> 00:35:12,320
Did he do the same thing to you?

469
00:35:13,240 --> 00:35:15,479
- Yes. - Oh dear.

470
00:35:15,480 --> 00:35:18,140
What a strange man.

471
00:35:29,420 --> 00:35:31,519
I was scared just now.

472
00:35:31,520 --> 00:35:34,480
You know I wasn't actually yelling at you, right?

473
00:35:35,230 --> 00:35:37,829
I know how to make copies.

474
00:35:37,830 --> 00:35:40,489
I did this a lot when I was an intern and a secretary.

475
00:35:40,490 --> 00:35:41,989
I know. I know.

476
00:35:41,990 --> 00:35:45,100
There's nothing you can't do, Director.

477
00:35:48,430 --> 00:35:50,220
So you understand.

478
00:35:53,740 --> 00:35:55,250
My stomach...

479
00:35:56,010 --> 00:35:57,349
Now yell at me.

480
00:35:57,350 --> 00:35:58,579
Say you were sorry before.

481
00:35:58,580 --> 00:36:00,640
Yell at me and scold me.

482
00:36:01,470 --> 00:36:03,749
How do you explain our being here then?

483
00:36:03,750 --> 00:36:06,399
But still, how can I yell at you?

484
00:36:06,400 --> 00:36:08,169
You used to be good at this.

485
00:36:08,170 --> 00:36:09,969
Are they fighting again?

486
00:36:09,970 --> 00:36:11,729
They seem close, too.

487
00:36:11,730 --> 00:36:13,290
Really.

488
00:36:15,540 --> 00:36:17,219
Director!

489
00:36:17,220 --> 00:36:20,449
A boss shouldn't take offense at things like that.

490
00:36:20,450 --> 00:36:23,899
You make a good boss by accepting criticism.

491
00:36:23,900 --> 00:36:27,100
Do you understand? I asked if you understood or not.

492
00:36:28,930 --> 00:36:30,289
Here we go again.

493
00:36:30,290 --> 00:36:33,129
I'm witnessing a legend right now, aren't I?

494
00:36:33,130 --> 00:36:35,689
Let's go downstairs before we get involved.

495
00:36:35,690 --> 00:36:37,900
Yes. I think that would be better.

496
00:36:47,280 --> 00:36:49,239
The office is dangerous. Let's go back immediately.

497
00:36:49,240 --> 00:36:51,099
Its...

498
00:36:51,100 --> 00:36:53,809
You're very good at improvisation.

499
00:36:53,810 --> 00:36:55,739
Very, very good.

500
00:36:55,740 --> 00:36:58,460
I had no other option.

501
00:36:59,240 --> 00:37:00,829
I was just pretending.

502
00:37:00,830 --> 00:37:02,850
Were your feelings hurt?

503
00:37:04,000 --> 00:37:06,439
Why are you so good at getting angry?

504
00:37:06,440 --> 00:37:09,269
Do you get angry when you see me?

505
00:37:09,270 --> 00:37:14,219
Why? Because I'm not older than you and I'm not your type?

506
00:37:14,220 --> 00:37:16,399
Why are you worried about such a comment?

507
00:37:16,400 --> 00:37:17,579
No.

508
00:37:17,580 --> 00:37:21,289
Didn't you prefer an older man?

509
00:37:21,290 --> 00:37:24,189
At the farm, you mentioned the age difference.

510
00:37:24,190 --> 00:37:29,169
You said I couldn't be your boyfriend and that you didn't see me as a man.

511
00:37:29,170 --> 00:37:31,120
That's what you said.

512
00:37:31,890 --> 00:37:34,020
THE...

513
00:37:36,930 --> 00:37:40,189
To be honest, my first love was younger than me.

514
00:37:40,190 --> 00:37:42,859
That's why I didn't want a younger man.

515
00:37:42,860 --> 00:37:44,630
Because of a bad memory.

516
00:37:47,330 --> 00:37:49,139
It's so frustrating.

517
00:37:49,140 --> 00:37:51,910
How can I make you feel better?

518
00:37:52,960 --> 00:37:55,369
You can do me a favor.

519
00:37:55,370 --> 00:37:57,059
Should I get you some chocolate milk?

520
00:37:57,060 --> 00:38:00,059
Or should I go to the arcade with you?

521
00:38:00,060 --> 00:38:02,079
Am I a child?

522
00:38:02,080 --> 00:38:03,600
In that case...

523
00:38:05,870 --> 00:38:09,110
You can't ask me for a kiss or anything like that.

524
00:38:10,940 --> 00:38:13,509
You're fond of this, aren't you?

525
00:38:13,510 --> 00:38:16,299
- What did you say? - Why would I want something like that?

526
00:38:16,300 --> 00:38:19,619
That's not true. Don't worry.

527
00:38:19,620 --> 00:38:22,159
I'll tell you when something comes to mind.

528
00:38:22,160 --> 00:38:24,110
Ok then.

529
00:38:29,100 --> 00:38:32,800
I don't need a favor to do things like this.

530
00:38:43,150 --> 00:38:45,640
[Yongsung Shopping Mall]

531
00:38:49,760 --> 00:38:54,269
Is this what he means by kindness?

532
00:38:54,270 --> 00:38:56,609
These are characters from my favorite comic books.

533
00:38:56,610 --> 00:38:59,660
Their names are easier to memorize than dog names.

534
00:39:02,960 --> 00:39:04,940
[Regis K. Landegre]

535
00:39:05,860 --> 00:39:07,630
Very jealous.

536
00:39:15,940 --> 00:39:17,990
I memorized them all.

537
00:39:21,010 --> 00:39:23,060
He memorizes quickly.

538
00:39:27,210 --> 00:39:28,880
Let's go.

539
00:39:33,370 --> 00:39:35,639
What are all these things?

540
00:39:35,640 --> 00:39:37,389
Is today a special day?

541
00:39:37,390 --> 00:39:39,499
How am I supposed to eat all of this...?

542
00:39:39,500 --> 00:39:42,719
Su Jeong, I have a boyfriend.

543
00:39:42,720 --> 00:39:44,889
Suddenly?

544
00:39:44,890 --> 00:39:46,959
When, where, and how did you meet?

545
00:39:46,960 --> 00:39:55,559
He was a client of mine, and I think we became very strongly connected, both physically and mentally.

546
00:39:55,560 --> 00:39:58,050
